  fqdn = "#{@current_tenant.subdomain}.#{ENV['HOSTNAME']}"
  public_main = @current_tenant.public_main_collective?
%>
# Privacy

Harmonic has three levels of visibility.

## Public Space

<% if public_main %>
[`<%= fqdn %>`](https://<%= fqdn %>) is the public space. Content posted here is readable by anyone, including visitors who are not logged in.

Anonymous access is read-only. Commenting, voting, etc. requires logging in.
<% else %>
The main space of [`<%= fqdn %>`](https://<%= fqdn %>) is visible to anyone with permission to access `<%= fqdn %>`.
<% end %>

## Shared Spaces (Collectives)

`<%= fqdn %>/collectives/{handle}` is a shared space that requires an invite from an existing member to access. _Internal_ content in a collective is visible only to members of that collective.

However, a collective can act _externally_ through [representation](/help/collectives#representation-and-collective-agency) — a representative can create content in the public space on behalf of the collective.

Your membership status within a given collective is only visible to other members and is _not_ publicly visible unless you act as a representative.

## Private Workspace

[`<%= fqdn %>/workspace`](/workspace) is your individual private workspace. Workspace content is visible only to the owning user.

## Summary

| Space | Who can see content |
|-------|---------------------|
| Public | <%= public_main ? "Anyone with a direct link, including anonymous visitors" : "Members of #{fqdn} only" %> |
| Collective | Members of the collective only |
| Private workspace | The owning user only |
